cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on identifying and characterizing malicious Facebook pages, which involves analyzing the content and behavior of these pages. This falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI), as well as cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social computing (cs.SOC). Additionally, the use of the Web of Trust API to determine domain reputations involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and the study of online behavior and communication (cs.CYBER).
